guangdong 's export of new high technology products amounts to us $ 3.76 billion in first two months of this year
xinhua news agency , guangzhou , march 16 ( reporter : chen ji ) -- latest statistic indicates that guangdong 's export of new high technology products amounts to us $ 3.76 billion , up 34.8 % over corresponding period and accounts for 25.5 % of the total exports of the province .
there are many bright signs in the export of new high technology products , which have significantly contributed to guangdong 's growth in foreign trades .
last year , guangdong 's export of new high technology products amounted to us $ 22.294 billion , up 31 % over corresponding period . this growth rate exceeded the province 's overall export growth rate by 27.2 % ; the net increase in export of new high technology products was us $ 5.27 billion . this had made up the decrease in export of traditional labor-intensive products due to price declines .
amongst guangdong 's export of new high technology products , computer and telecommunication products are doing exceptionally well . last year , their combined export amounted to us $ 19.14 billion , which was 85.9 % of the province 's total export of new high technology products .
the principal markets for guangdong 's new high technology products are hong kong , u.s.a. , european union and japan .
last year , the new high technology industry in zhu jiang delta exported us $ 21.99 billion of products , which accounted for 98.7 % of the province 's total export of new high technology products .
this year , the leading role is still very prominent .
at present , the self-supply rate of a whole set of computer is 95 % in the zhu jiang delta region . apart from the cpu , the region is capable of providing all parts in computer .
fifa will severely punish all cheating acts in the football field
xinhua news agency , beijing , march 17 -- in this year 's world cup , referees will adopt more severe measures against players that fish for benefits through diving etc . the message was revealed during a meeting of the executive committee of federation internationale de football association ( fifa ) held in switzerland on the 16th .
according to foreign news agencies , fifa indicated in a press release that they would fully support strict enforcement by referees , especially against those players that try to cheat the viewers .
the executive committee of fifa has also announced some changes .
fifa permits football players to take off their uniform to celebrate a score . the prerequisite is that such act will not interfere the normal proceeding of the game . however , fifa is seeing that vests or underclothes of players sometimes have words on them , which could trigger contradiction . fifa now stipulates that the vests of players must not have any writing on them . the new rule is to be effective from july 1 . fifa will also permit advertising on the sportswear of players . however , the advertisement must be on the front part of the sportswear .
suicide bombing in jerusalem
xinhua news agency , jerusalem , march 17 ( reporter : zhong cuihua , nie xiaoyang ) -- a man detonated a bomb that he was carrying next to a bus in a residential area in northern jerusalem in the afternoon of the 17th . the bomber was killed on the spot . nine men suffered minor injuries and were admitted hospital .
at this moment , police has sealed off the blast scene .
in less than two hours ago , a palestinian opened fire on pedestrians in kefar sava , a northern city of israel .
according to latest information , an israeli girl of 16 was killed and at least 12 were wounded .
police killed the gunman .
at this moment , no group has claimed responsibility for the shooting .
israel prime minister office condemns the shooting .
israeli prime minister sharon has indicated yesterday , israel will retaliate to any attack notwithstanding israel and palestinian authorities are attempting to reach a cease-fire .
a painting and calligraphy competition is held to celebrate the fifth anniversary of hong kong 's reversion
xinhua news agency , hangzhou , march 18 -- this year is the fifth anniversary of hong kong 's reversion and it also happens to be the first implementation of an " ethnic code for state civil servants " in china . to celebrate these two joyous occasions , a painting and calligraphy competition , with a competitive theme of " state civil servants -- public servants for the people " , is to be held for the civil servants in hong kong , macau and the mainland china .
hong kong 's wen wei po daily , the association of chinese mayors and hong kong cultural and entertainment council jointly sponsor the competition .
the participating public servants will create chinese paintings as well as calligraphy of poem and poetry to illustrate the scenic mountains and waters of china . they will also create calligraphies that incorporate ethnic codes , famous dictums , a motto or an aphorism , which proposes honesty , no bribery , hard working and dutiful spirits to be observed by all civil servants . the competition is to promote cultural accomplishments and professionalism amongst all civil servants .
the competition intends to protrude the joyous atmosphere of the fifth anniversary of hong kong 's reversion . it will also reveal the artistic charisma of chinese painting and calligraphy .
it is understood that the cut off date for submission of creations for this painting and calligraphy competition is set at april 20 , 2002 .
after evaluation , all works that receive a prize will be collected and published on the fifth anniversary day of hong kong 's reversion .
african national congress opposing sanctions against zimbabwe
xinhua news agency , johannesburg , march 18 ( reporter : gao yuan ) -- kgalema motlanthe , secretary general of south africa 's ruling party african national congress ( anc ) , criticizes the sanction against zimbabwe here on the 18th . anc regards the sanction as an attempt of western countries , including u.s. and england , to force zimbabwe to act according to their wishes .
in response to western countries ' threats of further sanctions against zimbabwe , motlanthe told the press : " who should be leading zimbabwe ? that is the business of the people of zimbabwe and should not be decided by western countries . "
he pointed out that every country in this world should observe the international principle of respecting sovereign rights of others . anc is firmly against any sanction by western countries against an independent sovereign state .
if western countries step up their sanctions against zimbabwe , it is not going to improve the situation but will accelerate the instability in zimbabwean communities .
he urged the zimbabwe government to cooperate with the opposing parties and jointly overcome difficulties including the shortage of food and the land crisis etc .
he emphasized that it is only through stronger unification can one defeat any attempt to split zimbabwe .
before this , anc has released a statement requesting international community to respect the choice of the people of zimbabwe and help them through any difficulties .
zimbabwean president robert mugabe was re-elected in a president election held during march 9 to 11th . however , western countries accuse serious frauds in the election . they do not think the election is free and fair thus refusing to accept the result . they also threaten to impose further sanctions against zimbabwe .
at present , certain western countries have already suspended their economic aids to zimbabwe .
before the election , european union is imposing " selective " sanctions against zimbabwe because its government is restricting press freedom and obstructing supervision work .
french paralympians return to paris with honor
xinhua news agency , paris , march 18 ( reporter : wang jingcheng ) -- after competing in the paralympic winter games held in salt lake city , usa , from march 7 to 16 , the french athletes have returned to paris today .
minister buffet of ministry of youth and sport , minister segolene royal with delegated responsibility for childhood and the family , and the disabled , and other parties concerned welcome the athletes warmly at the charles de gaulle airport .
this year , the french team has won a total of 19 medals in the 8th paralympic winter games in salt lake city , usa . out of the 19 medals , female athletes have won 9 medals including 1 gold and male athletes have won 10 medals of which one is gold .
this is the best accomplishment the french team has ever got in paralympic winter games .
at the welcoming ceremony , segolene royal said that french athletes have used their special performances to change the society 's opinion on them . french people appreciate their tremendous efforts in fighting out and changing people 's opinion on the disabled .
in his speech , minister buffet said that the french government would continue to support sport activities for the disabled as it did in the past .
jordan may come back as early as this sunday
xinhua news agency , washington , march 19 ( reporter : xie peilin ) -- " air " jordan may come back as early as this sunday after he recovers from his right knee surgery . however , the washington wizards may not be able to create too much an impact given that it is already near the end of the season .
jordan is stepping up a recovery warm-up , wizards ' coach doug collins said today . although he does not wish to appear in denver or salt lake city on wednesday and thursday , he may go to toronto this sunday . he may play for the wizards to challenge the raptors , which is not very much in shape at moment .
doug collins said , " he may appear any time . it really depends on how he feels . "
at present , his training is defense oriented but he also practices shots .
he is elevating the intensity to test whether his body can adapt to it .
so far as his knee is concerned , he thinks it heals a hundred percent after the surgery . "
jordan 's average score for the season is 24.3 point . he received his surgery three weeks ago , meanwhile , his team won 4 games and lost 8 .
at present , there are 15 regular matches left . the wizards won 31 and lost 36 and ranks 10th in the eastern conference . they are arrear of miami heat by half a game and lead the raptors by one game . however , they are arrear of charlotte hornets , in the eighth position , by two and half game .
coach doug collins naturally hopes that the comeback of jordan will lift the team 's performance or at least win several games in a short period of time such as to throw a gleam for after season games .
doug collins said , " without jordan 's absence , we could have won at least 3 more games .
given the current situation , he absolutely has the power to activate the team in time . "
south korea conveys its desire to resume talking with north korea
xinhua news agency , seoul , march 19 ( reporter : zhang li ) -- according to a report by yonhap news agency , south korea government has already made a request to megawati , the president of indonesia . it is hoped that she can convey to north korea leader kim jong-il that the south korea president kim dae-jung wishes to resume the talks between the two korea as well as the talks between north korea and u.s.
the content of the message is that south korea , u.s. and japan all wish to resolve conflicts with north korea through dialogues , an official of south korea said . it is hoped that north korea will adopt a more positive position .
it is reported that indonesia president megawati will visit north korea during march 28 to march 30 and then visiting south korea from march 30 to april 1 .
the south korea government has already sent the message to indonesia through diplomatic channels .
meanwhile , south korea government has denied the content of a report in " asahi newspaper " about megawati has passed on a hand written letter of kim dae-jung to kim jong-il .
european central bank forecasts accelerated economic rebound in euro area
xinhua news agency , brussels , march 20 ( reporter : wang xingqiao ) -- the chief economist of european central bank dr. otmar issing indicated here on the 20th that the economy in the euro area has already bottomed out and will start to rebound at a faster rate within this year ,
issing made the statement while attending a hearing held by the european council here in brussels .
" according to latest statistics , the economy in the euro area has started to rebound slowly since early this year . it is forecasted that the rebound will accelerate within this year " , he said .
it is forecasted that the economic growth in the euro area will reach 2 % to 2.5 % this year .
issing believes that the rebound in euro area is mainly caused by increases in consumptions and also because the inventory level of commodities has reached a very low level in the euro area .
when asked about inflation , he said , " the overall inflation rate in the euro area still exhibits a down trend . at present , there is no sign to show economic development in the medium term will create risks of price instability " .
when he talked about energy resources in the world , he said , " the recent increases in oil price in international markets have already created concerns to economic policy makers around the world . the impact of higher oil price to long-term economic developments should not be underestimated .
hong kong police discovered drug trafficking on the internet
xinhua news agency , hong kong , march 21 -- hong kong police has recently discovered drug trafficking activities on the internet .
the dangerous drug division of hong kong police department points out that this is the first discovery by the police and it is necessary to attach importance to it .
according to hong kong police , they have discovered several cases last year in which hong kong residents purchased ecstasy and other drugs through the internet . payments were made by credit cards .
drug dealers acquire drugs in thailand and then mail them to hong kong drug addicts .
yip lau-chuen of dangerous drug investigation division , hong kong police department pointed out that the majority of several cases discovered last year employed credit cards as the means of payment .
the hong kong police is cooperating with other relevant discipline forces to fight this kind of criminal activities .
a cross border drug trafficking forum has recently been held in hong kong . the person in charge of the commission of narcotic drugs of united nations has pointed out during the forum that drug trafficking on the internet is going to be a serious challenge to law enforcement agencies .
the security bureau of hong kong special administrative region has completed the consultation on computer crimes last year . the bureau is initiating some legislation changes in order to better control computer crimes .
african college students want new technologies to flow into africa
xinhua news agency , abidjan , march 21 ( reporter : song nan ) -- the second african higher education conference inaugurates on the 21st here in abidjan . the college students attending the conference urge the young people of africa to employ information and telecommunication technologies to tackle with the challenges of globalization in economy . the africa continent must not be left as a " border " to new technologies .
according to the chairman of the conference , new high technologies have promoted developments in asia , europe and america .
the arrival of the new era brings challenges and opportunities to the african continent . the young people in africa should strive to master new high technologies and make their contributions to create a better future for africa .
the theme of this year 's african higher education conference is " new technology , information and communication create more opportunities in new human resources training in africa " .
the conference will last for 3 days . delegates from more than 10 african higher education institutions and experts from enterprises will exchange ideas on several subjects , including " the future of africa and the technology challenge " , " cultural diversification and economic development " , " the outlook and opportunities of e-commerce in africa " etc .
during the conference period , a large cultural exhibition is also to be held at the same time .
indonesia reiterates : no foreign troops in country
xinhua news agency , jakarta , march 22 ( reporter : mai tangyuan ) -- indonesia ministry of foreign affairs has issued a press release that reiterates its position of no foreign troops in the island state .
the reiteration by indonesia ministry of foreign affairs is directed against a story in the march 20 " usa today " , which reports u.s. ' s intention to send troops to indonesia to help strike out members of the " al-qaeda " organization flee from afghanistan .
according to the announcement , the u.s. government has never made an official request to the indonesian government on the issue . the claim was later verified by a denial of the report by u.s. white house and the defense department .
the press release reiterates that indonesia pursues an active and independent foreign policy . indonesia has already developed close and beneficial cooperation against terrorism with foreign countries , including u.s.
ukraine condemned us for interfering its internal affairs .
xinhua news agency , kiev , march 22 , ( reporter zhang zhiqiang ) -- president leonid kuchma told the press that us house of representatives ' resolution is unprecedented and is " disturbing and puzzling " . he has condemned the u.s. for interfering with ukrainian internal affairs .
the us house of representatives has passed a resolution on march 20 urging the government of ukraine to ensure a democratic , transparent and fair election on march 31 .
the resolution also urges the government of ukraine to enforce the new election law impartially . in addition , the election result will indicate whether ukraine is to continue with its democratic reform .
" are we a nation , or are we a football playing field for strategic partners ? ukrainians must have their own dignity , " president kuchma said .
he also thanked askold lozynskyj , chairman of ukrainian world congress , who has sent a letter to the us congress .
" look at what you people have done ! " said lozynskyj in his letter .
" please mind your own business first before thinking of teaching others . "
ukrainian communist party leader petro symonenko also noted on the same day that the us action is a wanton interference in the internal affairs of ukraine . it is also a threat to the independency of ukraine .
viktor yushchenko , leader of the united social democratic party of ukraine , said the us house of representatives ' one-sided evaluation of ukrainian election activities would cause ukrainian political forces to split into two opposing extremes .
" the election of legislators for ukrainian supreme and local legislative institutions is purely an internal affair of ukraine " , the spokesman for ukrainian foreign affairs said on march 22 .
" in this final stage of ukrainian congressional election campaign , we hope foreign countries would adopt a prudent attitude and respect the standards of international laws . please do not interfere with the internal affairs of ukraine " , added the spokesman .
arabian countries unanimously oppose any u.s. attack on iraq
xinhua news agency , riyadh , march 23 -- according to a report in the " riyadh newspaper " on the 23rd , lebanon president emile lahoud made it clear that he opposes any u.s. attack on iraq during an interview by the newspaper . notwithstanding the arab summit has not commenced yet , it appears that arabian countries have adopted a unanimity position on the issue of iraq .
lahoud pointed that no arabian country can agree to any attack on any arabian countries by u.s. or its allies unless there is a proper reason for it . the u.s. must understand the consequences of such kind of attack . it does not matter what excuses or pretexts that u.s. may use .
lahoud thought that " war on terrorism " or " axis of evil " is attractive pretext that can usefully influence public opinion in western countries . however , no one should use such pretexts to carry out a crime .
he also urged u.s. not to adopt double standards . that is to fight terrorism in one region while ignoring the sovereign terrorism adopted by israel .
news in brief -- high-ranking official of south korea to visit north korea in april
xinhua news agency , beijing , march 25 -- according to information sources here , a spokeswoman of south korea presidential office announced on the 25th a visit to north korea by presidential envoy lim dong-won in the first week of april . lim , the special advisor on foreign relations , national security and unification to president kim dae-jung , will holds talks with north korea officials on the subject of resumption of family reunions and the reduction of tension between south and north .
according to the spokeswoman , south korea hopes that the talk will " lay the foundation " to resume dialogue between the two koreas . however , she did not give any specific details .
she said details of the talk will be released upon the return of lim dong-won from the north .
meanwhile , north korea central news agency also released a short statement about the upcoming visit of a special envoy of president kim dae-jung .
the statement said that the two sides will discuss the " serious condition " in the korean peninsula and other issues of common interests .
trial of indonesian speaker opens
xinhua news agency , beijing , march 25 -- according to the information available here , indonesia 's parliamentary speaker akbar tandjung appeared in court on march 25 in jakarta because he was prosecuted for corruption and dereliction of duty .
mr. tandjung is accused of illegal embezzlement of us $ 3.8 million aid fund that belongs to the state food agency bulog .
it is rumored that the fund was used by tandjung led golkar party to finance its election campaign in 1999 .
the aid fund was intended to help poor families that suffered from the financial crisis . however , investigators of the case found that the fund had never reached these families .
but tandjung has denied such allegation .
analysts said tandjung 's hope for becoming indonesian president would be undermined by this court case regardless of the trial results .
launch of " endeavour " delayed by robotic arm problems
xinhua news agency , washington , march 25 -- u.s. national aeronautics and space administration ( nasa ) announced on march 25 that the launch of space shuttle " endeavour " will be delayed from may 6 to may 31 . the international space station has a technical problem with the canadian-built robotic arm .
it is reported that " endeavour " will carry seven astronauts to the international space station during an 11-day space mission .
the crew of seven includes astronauts from france and russia .
a nasa spokesman pointed out that the crew in the international space station could utilize the ample time period to fix problems . however , the delay also means extra patience to the station crew because they have to stay in the international space station for another three weeks . american astronaut peggy whitson and two other russian astronauts will replace them , the spokesman added .
philippe perrin of france will be the first non-russian european astronaut flying to the space station . he will perform two space walks at the early stage of his mission .
shell 's investment in china will reach us $ 5 billion in 3 years time
xinhua news agency , beijing , march 26 ( reporter : qian chunxian ) -- the shell group 's total investment in china will reach us $ 5 billion by 2005 , wu zipei , the group 's chairman said a few days ago .
during the china development forum held here in beijing , he mentioned that shell 's total investment in china has already reached us $ 1.6 billion . in addition , the group is planning a number of new projects and total investment will reach us $ 5 billion by 2005 .
according to introduction , shell is currently negotiating a number of cooperation projects with chinese partners .
amongst these negotiations , the joint venture project with china petroleum & chemical group to build 500 gas stations in jiangsu is likely to take off this year .
shell has been doing businesses in china for over 100 years , wu zipei said .
the chinese market has huge potential and is an important part in shell 's global strategy .
china 's energy demand is forecasted to double before 2020 in tandem with its economy developments . by that time , china will be consuming 16 % of the total energy resources in the world .
china is facing serious challenges in energy resources . a diversification in energy sources is important to ensure stable supply as well as for environmental protection . shell will play an important role in this transition process .
xinhua news agency , united nations , march 26 ( reporter : gu zhen-qiu ) -- the spokesman of united nations ( un ) announced on the 26th that un security council will send a delegation to the democratic republic of congo ( congo ) as well as other countries involved in a conflict with congo . the delegation will leave on april 27 and intends to create new momentums to the peace process in congo .
according to the spokesman , the delegation comprises of representatives of the 15 members of the security council and the french ambassador to un will be the delegation chief .
the principal objective of this visit is to maintain dialogue with the leaders involved in the congo conflict and convince them to observe the 1999 peace agreement signed in lusaka , the capital city of zambia .
this is the third security council delegation to africa 's great lake region since may 2000 .
sri lanka government to hold peace talks with tamil tigers
xinhua news agency , colombo , march 27 ( reporter : zhang yadong ) -- the sri lanka government announced on march 27 that it plans to hold peace talks with the liberation tigers of tamil eelam in early may . sri lanka wants to end the nearly 20-year long bloody tribal conflicts on the island .
the spokesman for sri lanka justice , law reform & national integration ministry gl pieris said in a press conference on march 27 that the government and the tamil tigers agreed to start peace talks as early as possible . pieris added that the government is hoping to hold talks in the first week of may .
the initial talks are going to lay groundwork for more concrete talks , he added .
sri lanka government has not announced the venue for the talks as yet but reports suggest the talks might be held in thailand .
pieris said the government plans to hold talks with the tamil tigers in an asian country and is undergoing relevant preparation works .
meanwhile , tamil tigers ' chief negotiator anton balasingham and its leader velupillai prabhakaran have ended their three-year long exile in london . they have returned to the northern part of sri lanka , which is under the control of the tamil tigers . they recently held meetings there with the norwegian special envoy erik solheim and the norwegian ambassador to sri lanka .
the tamil tigers said after the meeting that they would restart peace talks with the government when the situation in the region they controlled becomes normal again . however , the tamil tigers still insist that sri lanka government have to cancel the ban on their activities .
the sri lanka government and the tamil tigers signed an agreement for permanent ceasefire in february , laying the foundation for their peace talks .
china unicom records a 38 % jump in net profits last year
xinhua news agency , hong kong , march 27 ( reporter : li kai ) - the hong kong listed china unicom ltd. announces here today that the businesses of china unicom have achieved outstanding results in 2001 . total turnover has reached rmb 29.393 billion . the realized net profits amount to rmb 4.457 billion , up 38 % over the preceding year .
china unicom is one of the integrated telecommunication service providers in china . the company provides many different communication services including mobile telecommunication , domestic and international long distance service , data , internet and paging etc .
according to china unicom , the company has provided 6.41 billion minutes of long distance calls for public switched telephone network and ip phones , which is an increase of 5.9 times over the preceding year . the company 's market share has increased from the 1.3 % in 2000 to 7.7 % . the total connected time for international calls has increased by 3.4 times over the preceding year .
according to yang xianzu , chief executive officer of china unicom , the company will continue to step up its mobile telecommunication business . the strategy this year is a differentiated approach such as to ensure a balance growth for both cdma and gsm mobile services . this way the company can continue to enjoy a better growth in terms of number of mobile phone customers .
the central banks of china and japan signed a currency reciprocal agreement
xinhua news agency , tokyo , march 28 ( reporter : wang yan ) -- the governor of people 's bank of china , dai xiang-long , and the governor of bank of japan , masaru hayami , have signed a bilateral currency reciprocal agreement for renminbi and japanese yen in tokyo on the 28th .
according to the agreement , bank of china and bank of japan will provide a conversion of the other side 's currency to the equivalent of us $ 3 billion when necessary . the purpose is to help maintain the stability of the financial markets .
the signing of the currency reciprocal agreement between china and japan indicates further cooperation between the two central banks .
the agreement with japan is china 's second currency reciprocal agreement . in december 2001 , bank of china has signed a us $ 2 billion agreement with bank of thailand .
china intends to sign more currency reciprocal agreements with other countries including south korea etc. in the near future .
according to dai xiang-long , china is actively participating in financial cooperation in asia . china is willing to cooperate with other asian countries and regions to guard against risks and maintain economic and financial stability in the region .
china 's ambassador to japan , wu da-wei , attended the currency reciprocal agreement signing ceremony between people 's bank of china and bank of japan .
earthquake victims start reconstruction in afghanistan
xinhua news agency , kabul , march 28 ( reporter : pan yunzhao ) -- in the northern province of baghlan , earthquake victims have started to rebuild their homes just three days after the quakes .
rebecca richards , spokeswoman of un office for the coordination of humanitarian affairs , told xinhua that afghan interim government , un agencies and other ngos have formed a core committee to conduct an evaluation of the affected areas . they found victims have already started to rebuild their houses . some of them are actually using materials provided by aid agencies .
in view of this , un aid agencies are starting to consider appropriate assistance to help earthquake victims rebuild their houses , richards added .
the aid organizations have stockpiled large amount of aid materials and are distributing them to victims through land and air modes .
the nahrin and burka areas of the baghlan province in afghanistan suffered most in the violent earthquakes . the disaster caused heavy losses in human lives and tens of thousands were left homeless .
japan temporarily suspends humanitarian aids to russia
xinhua news agency , tokyo , march 29 -- japan 's minister for foreign affairs yoriko kawaguchi announced a temporary suspension of humanitarian aids to russia on the 29th . the measure will continue until the restructure of the international committee responsible for granting aids is completed .
according to yoriko kawaguchi , japanese government is to limit the amount of funding to the committee and hence to russia . only staffing expenditure of the committee and one technology cooperation project in russia will continue to be funded . the measure will apply until the restructure is completed .
the suspension is made in response to recent comments by finance minister masajuro shiokawa .
masajuro shiokawa thinks that the fiscal position of japanese government has continued to decline . therefore , he has recently urged cabinet members to ensure all funds are wisely spent .
it is understood that deputy chief cabinet secretary suzuki muneo has improperly pressured the foreign office in the russian project . when the improper application procedure is revealed , the committee is condemned for not doing their job and also for lack of transparency in the usage of funds .
european union will hold consultations with china on the upcoming temporary safeguard measures on steel products
xinhua news agency , beijing , march 29 ( reporter : ju yuming ) -- " china is concerned about the european union 's upcoming temporary safeguard measures on some steel products " , the minister of foreign trade and economic cooperation shi guangsheng said here in beijing yesterday . european union ( eu ) has made a positive reaction and indicates that they will arrange to hold consultations with china as soon as possible . eu has treated china as a developing country and may make some special arrangements to properly deal with the issue .
shi guangsheng made the above statement in response to a question by a reporter while attending a working committee meeting on nation-wide economic and foreign trade legislation .
he said , " the current trade war on steel is becoming more intense and the basic problem originated from u.s. "
at present , all affected countries are criticizing the u.s. " 201 steel bill " and have made requests for bilateral consultations . some countries have even proposed to resolve the conflict through world trade organization .
on march 27 , eu has decided to impose temporary safeguard measures against imports covering 15 types of steel products . china has made a prompt response to that . shi guangsheng has written a letter to eu trade commissioner pascal lamy to express deep concern and proposes a bilateral negotiation with eu .
train and car collision killed 7 in liaoning
xinhua news agency , chenyang , march 30 ( reporter : wang jun ) -- a car collided with a train in jinzhou shi , liaoning , at 14 : 13 hours on march 29 . the incidence caused 7 deaths and 3 seriously injured .
according to the introduction by the safety inspection office of chenyang railway department , a four-wheel agricultural vehicle tried to rush through a railway crossing between lijia gou and zhoujia tun district when it collided with a train traveling from jinzhou to chengde .
the vehicle was illegally carrying 14 passengers together with 50 bags of chemical fertilizer and seeds at time of the accident .
during the collision , 4 passengers jumped off the vehicle and were not injured . the remaining 10 passengers were either injured or killed . the blocking rod at the crossing was damaged and the train also suffered some damages .
after the incident , the ministry of railway , chenyang railway department , jinzhou shi and local government officials rushed to the scene and dealt with the necessary arrangements .
the general secretariat of the league of arab states had an urgent meeting at its headquarters on the situation of palestine .
permanent representatives of twenty-two member states attended the meeting .
the arab league 's secretary general amr moussa told a press conference after the meeting that israel 's escalated military operations against palestine have clearly demonstrated israel 's rejection of the peace process .
what is happening is an extension of israeli military occupation in palestine , he added . the palestine people will continue its resistance against israeli invasion .
moussa said , " as long as the israeli military occupation of the palestinian territory exists for a day , as long as the israeli tanks and soldiers exist on the palestinian territory for a day , palestinian people 's resistance will persist for another day . "
xinhua news agency , jerusalem , march 31 ( reporter : zhong cuihua , nie xiaoyang ) -- israel 's security cabinet decided to step up military actions in palestinian controlled territory in the evening of 31st . israel will also advance the timing of a series of planned military operations .
prime minister ariel sharon called a cabinet meeting in the afternoon of 31st to discuss the situation between israel and palestinian . the cabinet discussed on how to deal with the increasing bomb attacks by palestinian . the meeting decided to increase military actions against palestinian .
according to sources in the political circles , the security cabinet is of the opinion that more military actions can only weaken the activities of terrorists but cannot fundamentally eliminate this kind of attacks .
sharon has given a nationwide televised address at 8 : 30 pm on 31st ( beijing time : april 1 , 01 : 30 hours ) to explain to his people the position of the government in dealing with the conflicts between israel and palestinian .
cambodia and vietnam jointly sponsor a commodities fair
xinhua news agency , phnom penh , april 1 ( reporter : yan ming ) -- a commodities fair co-sponsored by vietnam inaugurated here on the 1st . more than 200 commercial products are shown .
the fair comprises of 55 pavilions set up by 50 enterprises from cambodia and vietnam .
commodities displayed include motorcycles , electric home appliances , agricultural utensils , pharmaceuticals , beverages , processed food and garments etc .
during the inauguration ceremony , vietnamese ambassador to cambodia nguyen duy hung said that there are great potentials in economic and trade development between vietnam and cambodia . the commodities fair will help promote economic cooperation and enhance trade volume between the two countries .
according to nguyen , bilateral trades show gratifying progress . trade volume between the two countries has increased from us $ 0.169 billion in 2000 to us $ 0.18 billion in 2001 .
" it is a great thing for cambodia and vietnam to develop economics and trades hand in hand . the effort will benefit the economies of the two countries . it can promote economic development of asean as well . this help prepare the cambodia and vietnam economies for an early integration with asean and the global economy " , cambodia minister of trade cham prasit said .
indonesian badminton expert regards taufik hidayat 's ranking advantageous
xinhua news agency , jakarta , april 1 ( reporter : mai tangyuan ) -- alisanto , chairman of the badminton club of kuduz in central java , indonesia , told a reporter of antara news wire on april 1 in the provincial capital semarang that men 's singles player taufik hidayat 's world ranking is very advantageous for indonesia 's defense of its thomas cup title .
taufik , now ranked 33rd , might play in the second or third singles and his physiological burden will be lighter than playing in the first singles .
in the group competition , a win in the first singles can affect later competitions or at least affect fellow teammates ' feeling and encourage them to win .
however , if the indonesians lose in the first singles , taufik , playing in the second or third singles , will have the chance to win . the final match result will then be decided by the two doubles .
indonesia 's chance of defending the thomas cup title has been increased after the return of taufik since the young player is a very strong player in the world , the club chairman said .
alisanto believes the return of taufik to the indonesian national team gives indonesia hopes to defeat opponents including host china .
a badminton web site survey have found that 45 % of the respondents said indonesia might be able to defend their thomas cup title , 21 % believed china could be the champion while 17 % considered malaysia to have the best chance , according to a press report .
georgia is to withdraw troops from kodori gorge
xinhua news agency , moscow , april 2 -- news in tbilisi : the delegates of united nations ( un ) , georgia , abkhazia and peace keeping troops of commonwealth of independent states signed an agreement for georgia to withdraw troops from kodori gorge on april 2 in tbilisi .
according to itar-tass , the agreement stipulated a withdrawal of georgia troops from kodori gorge before april 10 . at the same time , peacekeeping troops and un observers will resume patrols in the area . all sides are to ensure the safety of residents in the region .
the representative of un secretary general 's special representative dieter boden to georgia regarded the agreement as a " positive sign " because it revealed a willingness of georgia and abkhazia to resolve their conflicts through compromises .
he said the document paved way for further dialogues .
in 1992 , local authorities of abkhazia in georgia demanded independence from georgia and caused military conflicts with georgia authorities .
last october , the two sides had several conflicts in the kodori gorge and georgia government deployed troops to the conflict area .
xinhua news agency , ankara , april 2 ( reporter : huai chengbo ) -- according to a report by anadolu news agency , turkey 's minister of foreign affairs ismail cem said on the 2nd that a new step on the basis of the madrid agreement is required . the madrid agreement has been the main pillar of the middle east peace process . the minister made the comment during a discussion in turkey 's parliament on the subject of israel 's invasion of palestinian cities in west bank of jordan river .
" u.s. should take immediate action to end the killing and also the enormous pain between the palestinian and israeli people " , ismail said .
he also emphasized that u.s. should carry out her own function . in addition , u.s. must treat palestine and israel equally .
as to turkey 's position in the middle east problem , he said , " middle east has an important strategic meaning to turkey . therefore , turkey wishes to see peace and stability in the region " .
he reiterated turkey 's support to the recent un security council resolution on palestine and israel conflict .
the resolution calls for a ceasefire between palestine and israel and the withdrawal of israeli troops from ram allah and other palestinian cities .
according to another report , turkey has already consulted palestine , israel and other middle east courtiers including egypt , saudi arabia and jordan on the convention of an international meeting on middle east problems .
the middle east peace meeting convened in madrid , spain in 1990 has already established a principle of " land for peace " .
under the guidance of this principle , palestine and israel have already signed a declaration in principle of palestine self-rule in washington in 1993 .
ntt communications injects more funds to an internet company
xinhua news agency , tokyo , april 3 -- the spokesman of ntt communications , a subsidiary of nippon telegraph and telephone corporation , said on april 3 that they will continue to support the business development of verio , an internet company with its headquarter in u.s. ntt communications will inject an additional us $ 305 million into verio .
according to the spokesman , ntt communications estimates that verio will need at least us $ 305 million this year to cover deficits . ntt communications is willing to provide the necessary funding and intends to provide continuing funding support to verio until such time the company turns around its loss position .
it is understood that verio , a colorado company , is an internet services provider . it provides high speed internet , e-commerce , private network and web site maintenance services mainly to corporations .
nippon telegraph and telephone corporation purchased the company in 2000 for us $ 5.5 billion .
in the past several years , verio has never made any money . ntt communications has already injected us $ 2.16 billion into the company in several funding arrangements .
liberian rebels close in to the capital
xinhua news agency , lagos , march 25 -- according to information sources in monrovia : liberian military said the fight between government troops and armed rebels intensified in the past week . the fight has advanced to a strategic road and a government military camp about 35 kilometers from the capital , monrovia .
in february this year , the rebels have also attacked kley , which is about the same distance to the capital as the current attempt .
the military camp is located at todee , which is right on a strategic road from monrovia to cote d 'ivoire and guinea .
the current fight broke out at daybreak on february 28th right after united nations ( un ) investigation of alleged trading of diamonds for weapons by liberian government . un has since imposed sanctions on liberia .
the liberians united for reconciliation and democracy ( lurd ) has stepped up their efforts to overthrow taylor 's government or otherwise force him to step down .
according to a senior official in government military , the principal objective of lurd 's military operations is to take over the diamond producing areas . it is because lurd needs more money to buy more weapons . they also need money to solve the economic difficulties that they are facing .
lurd has commenced their war against the liberian president taylor in 2000 .
xinhua news agency , united nations , april 4 ( reporter : ding baozhong ) -- catherine bertini , executive director of united nations ( un ) world food programme ( wfp ) said here in new york on april 4 that wfp has become the largest humanitarian aid organization in the world . wfp has distributed nearly us $ 1.7 billion in food assistance in different corners of the world in 2001 .
while making her summary report on the activities and functions of wfp to un security council , bertini pointed out wfp has extended a helping hand to different areas suffering from disasters and / or conflicts in different parts of the world . wfp has saved many lives and contributes to the re-construction in some countries . wfp 's efforts can help stabilize situations in regions with conflicts .
according to her , wfp has provided us $ 240 million in food assistance to afghanistan and millions of afghans have benefited under the program .
bertini urged donor countries to be more generous in order that wfp can properly complete its mission in afghanistan in 2002 .
she indicated wfp 's plan requires us $ 285 million but only us $ 70 million has been raised this far .
bertini also urged the un system and its member countries to pay more attention to personal safety of un workers whilst in their course of executing humanitarian missions . all countries must punish criminals that ever attempt to harm any un workers .
according to statistic , 204 un officials are injured since 1992 but only 15 criminals have ever been apprehended .
germany presents section of berlin wall to united nations
xinhua news agency , beijing , april 5 -- the government of germany presented three sections of the berlin wall , a symbol of the cold war between east and west , to united nations ( un ) on april 4 .
according to foreign news report , each of the the three wall fragments has a height of approximately 3.6 meters and weights 2.8 tons . the fragments are decorated with a painting of a man and a woman embracing across the top of the wall .
the three wall fragments were shipped to new york last october in memory of the unification of the two germanys .
as the un park on the east bank of new york has been closed since " 9.11 " , the public is precluded from viewing the fragment there .
during the presentation of the gift , un secretary general kofi annan said that the end of confrontation between east and west made it clear : " peace is always achievable ; that is so even in the middle east . "
the president of germany 's bundestag , wolfgang thierse told annan that there was a wall in many people 's mind well before the construction of the berlin wall was completed .
the berlin wall has finally become history and the germans are not the only ones that benefit from the wall 's fall .
bill gates fooled on the april fools ' day
xinhua news agency , beijing , april 5 -- the well-known microsoft chairman bill gates was duped into a big joke on april fools ' day by a canadian radio station .
marc-antoine audette and sebastien trudel of ckmf-fm , a quebec canada radio station , called bill gates by the phones on april 1 and represented themselves as the canadian prime minister . the two imitated chretien 's voice and talked closely with gates for more than 10 minutes .
they talked with gates about world economy and the defects of " windows " operating system . at the same time , bill gates was invited to visit quebec at an appropriate time .
the radio station played the recording of the conversation twice in entertainment programs on the evening of april 2 . the station has re-played the recording the next day due to requests of audiences .
after the joke , audette said he never thought it was so easy to connect to bill gates . gates ' assistants never discovered or even thought of the possibility of an april fools ' day joke .
after knowing the fact , the spokesman of microsoft said , " the radio station has forged some documents in order to lead microsoft to ' firmly believe ' that they are employees of canadian government . " the spokesman warned that the " joke " might look amusing but it was a bit too much .
it is understood that the radio station has also fooled celine dion and other celebrities on april fools ' day .
xinhua news agency , ankara , april 5 ( reporter : huai chengbo ) -- on april 5 here in ankara , afghan interim authority chairman hamid karzai renewed a request to expand the operating areas of the international peacekeeping force to areas beyond the capital city of kabul .
when hamid karzai concluded his two days visit to turkey , he told reporters at the airport , " afghans outside the capital city of kabul would like to see the expansion and extension of peacekeeping force as a guarantee for continued security . "
earlier this year , karzai has requested the security council of united nations to expand the operating areas of the peacekeeping troops as well as to consider deployment of troops to countryside areas .
he said that an expansion of operations would signal a global commitment to a country brutalized by 23 years of war .
turkey agreed in principle to take over the command of the peacekeeping troops in afghanistan from england .
however , turkey is concerned about the security in areas outside kabul and is against the idea to expand the operating areas of peacekeeping troops .
u.s. has already indicated its support for turkey 's position .
karzai has dismissed concerns that turkish troops might be dragged into unrest in areas outside kabul .
however , he also indicated that afghanistan was prepared to accept whatever decision the international peacekeeping might have .
northern china is facing another sand storm
xinhua news agency , beijing , april 6 ( reporter : dong jun ) -- the central weather bureau issued a " sand and dust storm warning " in its 6 pm forecast this afternoon . sand and dusty weather is expected between this evening and tomorrow in the east part of northwest china , majority areas of northern china as well as in central and south part of the northeast plain .
according to the forecast , central , east and southern part of inner mongolia , northern part of the three provinces of shaanxi , shanxi and hebei , western part of the two provinces of liaoning and jilin may all be affected by the sand storm . part of the regions may experience violent sand storm . part of the huanghuai region may experience dust flow and drifting sand . the aforesaid areas may also face an accompanying wind in between 5 to 7 on the wind scale . temperature may decrease by 6 to 12 degrees centigrade . in some areas , temperature may drop by as much as 14 degrees centigrade .
the beijing city was sunny this morning but strong wind appeared in the afternoon . the change in weather forced most people that were originally in outdoor activities to move back to their homes .
notwithstanding the central weather bureau issued a forecast of strong wind in northern china last evening , a lot of residents still went out this morning because the sky looked clear especially after some spring rain earlier .
hohhot , the capital of inner mongolia autonomous region also experienced strong wind and a sharp fall in temperature today .
however , the sky remained clear under the strong north wind .
according to experts , most areas in inner mongolia had some spring rain yesterday . in urban hohhot , the rainfall was 33 millimeters . the rain had greatly reduced the drought situation and helped restrain any sand storm attack .
china 's telecommunication market will worth 1 thousand billion yuan by 2005
xinhua news agency , shanghai , april 6 ( reporter : ping yizhen ) -- according to the officials from the ministry of information technology attending the sino-russia information and telecom seminar here in shanghai , china 's telecommunication market will have a value of 1,050 billion yuan by 2005 . that is 2.5 times the value of year 2000 .
according to forecast , the number of telephone users in china is expected to grow at an annual average rate of 26 % during the " tenth five-year " plan . in eastern china , the growth rate is expected to be 24 % . in central china , the growth rate is expected to be 26 % while the growth rate in western china is expected to be 30 % .
total telephone users in china will reach 500 million by 2005 . that is an availability rate of 40 % .
the customer profile for china 's mobile phone service will shift towards ordinary consumers . mobile services will also migrate from simple messaging services to data exchange , multimedia over medium or high-speed connection and interactive multimedia over high-speed connection .
internet services will continue to be a high growth sector in china 's telecommunication services . the demand is likely to move from narrow bandwidth to wide bandwidth . classification and point based broadcast model may move towards interactive services . the user group may expand from medium and large cities to cover principal cities in rural areas .
in the " tenth five-year " , china 's data and multimedia internet users is expected to grow at an annual average rate of 70 % .
by 2005 , the number of internet users in china is estimated to be 200 million .
annan will discuss middle east situation with u.s. , russia and european union
xinhua news agency , madrid , april 7 ( reporter : liu ruichang ) -- according to a report in spain 's " albacete newspaper " on the 7th , united nations ( un ) secretary-general kofi annan is expected to meet on the 10th with u.s. secretary of state colin powell , spanish foreign minister josep pique representing the rotating presidency of the european union , european security chief javier solana , and russian foreign minister igor ivanov . the " quartet " meeting will discuss the israeli-palestinian conflict , which is getting worse everyday .
this information was disclosed by annan during an interview by the newspaper in un headquarter .
the special report was published the same day in " albacete newspaper " .
during the interview , annan talked about un 's function in the resolution of the military conflict between palestine and israel . so far , un has played an active role and un security council has passed two important resolutions , 1397 and 1402 , for the resolution of israeli-palestinian conflict .
" he will use the opportunity of the meeting on the 10th and discuss the serious situations in middle east with the senior leaders from u.s. , european union and russia . " , annan said .
it is understood that annan will inaugurate the un second world assembly on aging together with spanish prime minister jose maria aznar on the 8th . colin powell will arrive spain next week on official visit . powell will sign an extension agreement on military cooperation between u.s. and spain . igor ivanov is making a special trip to spain to meet powell and intends to discuss bilateral relationship with him .
u.s. loses billions in computer crimes last year
xinhua news agency , washington , april 7 -- according to the " 2001 computer crime and security survey " released on the 7th , computer crime is ' soaring ' . computer crime has cost u.s. corporations and government departments billions of dollars and shows massive increases over year 2000 .
there are numerous reports of computers infected by virus , denial of service attacks and all kinds of security holes in systems across u.s.
according to 538 computer security experts in business , government agencies and universities , u.s. businesses and other organizations are paying high prices in computer crimes each year .
while most organizations were reluctant to put a figure on their financial loses , 35 % surveyed said security breaches in 2001 had cost them $ 377m , compared to $ 265m in 2000 .
the survey was conducted by the computer security institute and the federal bureau of investigation and did not include assessment of losses by individuals in america .
berber language recognized as an official language of algeria
xinhua news agency , algiers , april 8 ( reporter : xu donghua ) -- a joint meeting of both chambers of algerian congress has considered and approved a draft amendment to constitution initiated by president abdelaziz bouteflika . the proposed amendment is to make the berber language an official language under constitution .
prime minister ali benflis pointed out in the meeting that the approval of the draft indicated that cultural diversity in algeria is confirmed by laws and this is good for promoting national unity of algeria .
the berbers are natives of northern africa . berbers living in algeria have now accounted for one-sixth of the country 's total population .
since independence , the arabic has been the only language recognized by constitution but berbers object the arrangement .
serious unrests flared up last april in the northeastern area of kabylie where many berbers inhabit there .
some 60 berbers were killed and more than 200 injured during the three-month unrests .
local people there have been demanding the berber language to be recognized as an official language in the constitution of algeria .
on march 12 this year , president bouteflika made a national television announcement , in which he pledged to satisfy the berbers ' demand by amending the constitution .
white house welcomes israel 's first withdrawal from west bank
xinhua news agency , washington , april 8 -- white house spokesman fleischer released a statement on the evening of the 8th , which described israel 's withdrawal from two west bank cities , tulkarm and qalqilya , as " a start " . all parties in the middle east should assume their own responsibilities .
in a brief written statement , fleischer said : " it is a start .
as president bush said on the 4th , all parties still have their own responsibilities . the president wants all parties to step up their efforts . "
the israel army will pull out from tulkarm and qalqilya at daybreak on the 9th . at present , israel has not given a timetable of its withdrawal from other west bank cities .
bush reiterated to reporters in tennessee the other day that israel must withdraw from palestinian areas without further delay . he emphasized that he " really mean it " .
bush said that he already told israel 's prime minister sharon the u.s. demand . he was waiting for israel 's immediate withdrawal .
bush : nato must forge a new relationship with russia
xinhua news agency , beijing , april 10 -- according to information received here , u.s. president bush received the visiting nato secretary-general lord robertson in the white house on the 9th.president bush told lord robertson that nato must " forge a new relationship with russia . "
bush thought that through a constructive relationship , " we can finally and forever abolish the divisions that are relics of a previous era . "
during the meeting , bush and lord robertson discussed a series of problems and among them , the issue of iraq and the expansion of nato .
bush said , " nato must develop new , flexible capabilities to meet the threats of the 21st century .
we must also take on new members . "
bush did not directly talk about iraq when speaking with reporters after the meeting with lord robertson .
however , he said , " we will consult closely with our allies as we move forward in the war against terrorism . "
robertson said , " the president and i discussed the common threats that we face , both in europe and in north america , including from weapons of mass destruction . "
he said , " nato allies will work together to overcome these threats and is going to succeed . "
mexican president 's u.s. trip vetoed by senate
xinhua news agency , mexico city , april 9 -- according to the spokesman of mexican senate , mexican president vicente fox 's plan to visit u.s. and canada in the middle of april was vetoed by senate .
this is the first time in history of mexico that a president 's foreign visit plan has been vetoed by senate .
according to the spokesman , 71 senators voted in favor and 41 voted against and hence the president 's visit was vetoed .
the opposing senators believed that the president had to place more efforts in internal affairs and should not be over zealous about visits .
last year , president fox has made 15 visits .
one of the senators , who voted against the trip , did so because the principal objective of president fox 's visit was to talk to mexicans emigrated to u.s.
according to reports , president fox 's visit plan will be submitted to the chamber of deputies after the veto .
if the plan is vetoed again , then his trip will be cancelled .
if it is approved , the senate will vote on it again .
the original plan of president fox is to visit seattle on april 15 . he will meet with bill gates , chairman of microsoft as well as the mexican immigrants community there .
he will then fly to vancouver and calgary , canada and hold meetings with local businessmen and academic circles . the visit is intended to last for 3 days .
track-and-field competition starts to unfold in the west asian games
xinhua news agency , kuwait , april 10 ( reporter : an jiang ) -- since the inauguration of the west asian game , about half of all competitions have already taken place . however , track-and-field competitions have not started until today .
contestants from twelve countries participate in this year 's athletic games . they will compete for gold medals in seven events in the first day competition .
on april 9 , kuwait has marginally beaten qatar in basketball with a score of 97 : 93 and won this year 's championship .
syria has beaten iran with a score of 110 : 92 and the iran team ended in the third place in basketball .
in football competition , kuwait has to win today 's match against palestine , a team long regarded as a " black horse " , before it has a chance to compete for the championship .
the kuwait media calls the match as a " bottleneck " contest , which is going to decide the success or failure of kuwait team .
the syria football team has beaten iran with a closed score of 33 : 32 . today , it will compete with kuwait for the gold medal .
up till april 9 , kuwait has won 19 gold medals , 18 silver medals and 12 copper medals . with 49 medals in hand , kuwait is leading the game and is followed in turn by iran , syria , saudi arabia , qatar and jordan .
powell says it is important that he meets arafat
xinhua news agency , madrid , april 10 -- u.s. state of secretary colin powell has said here on the 10th that meeting with palestinian leader yasser arafat is " important " in his middle east peace mission . he hopes there will be no difficulty in arranging a meeting with arafat .
powell indicated the position after discussion with officials from european union , russia and united nations .
" arafat is the leader of palestinian people . i think palestinian people and leaders of arabian countries regard him as the person that israel must deal with , " he said .
according to foreign reports , u.s. white house spokesman fleischer has said in washington on the same day that israel has assured u.s. there will be a meeting with arafat in powell 's middle east peace mission .
israeli defense minister binyamin ben-eliezer has told reporters on the same day in the west bank city jenin that israel will not prevent powell to talk with arafat later this week .
there was originally no meeting with arafat in powell 's middle east peace mission .
palestinian official indicated that if powell refused to meet arafat then no palestinian representative could possibly talk with him .
when powell was in morocco and egypt , leaders of arabian countries emphasized again if powell does not meet with arafat in his trip to the region then he cannot possibly obtain any result .
former serbian interior minister , vlajko stojiljkovic , attempts to commit suicide
xinhua news agency , belgrade , april 11 ( reporter : yang chengming ) -- vlajko stojiljkovic , a former serbian interior minister and a current deputy in the yugoslav assembly chamber of republics , shot himself in the head outside the yugoslav parliament in the evening of april 11 . the hague tribunal wants stojiljkovic for alleged war crimes .
he was rushed to the hospital and is still in critical condition .
stojiljkovic said in a note , which has been released after his suicide attempt , " i , vlajko stojiljkovic , a deputy in the yugoslav assembly chamber of republics , express my protest against members of the current puppet dos ( democratic opposition of serbia ) authorities .
i condemn them over their reckless violation of constitution and laws of this country . i condemn their attempt to destroy this country and their tread on our national dignity . "
yugoslav president vojislav kostunica issued an announcement on that evening . kostunica said stojiljkovic 's suicide was a warning towards the western countries , which have continuously exerted pressure and made new demands on yugoslavia .
chamber of republics and chamber of citizens of the yugoslav assembly passed the law of cooperation between yugoslavia and hague tribunal on march 10 and 11 respectively .
according to the law , all people wanted by the hague tribunal for alleged war crimes before the law was passed , irrespective of their nationality , will be extradited to the hague tribunal as long as they are found on the yugoslav territory .
that means stojiljkovic will also be extradited to hague according to the law .
saudi arabia conducted a fund-raising campaign for palestinian
xinhua news agency , riyadh , april 12 -- saudi arabia conducted a fund raising campaign for the support of palestinian . the countrywide telethon started from 4 pm on april 11 and ran up till 3 am on april 12 .
saudi state television established 30 hotlines and put together 15 computers to process donations .
the television station also assembled a 25-man team to receive donors who came to the station in person to make donation .
the campaign raised 210 million riyals ( us $ 56 million ) in cash and also a large quantity of chattels .
the king of saudi arabia took the lead and donated 10 million riyals . crown prince abdullah donated 5 million riyals ( us $ 1.34 million ) . the famous entrepreneur of saudi arabia , prince alwaleed donated 100 million riyals ( us $ 26.7 million ) .
there was a long line of cars right outside the television station waiting to make donations notwithstanding the 11th and 12th were actually a holiday and it was raining cats and dogs .
employees ' of many companies and enterprises also donated their salary for one day to the campaign .
east timor presidential campaign ends
xinhua news agency , jakarta , april 12 -- according to local media here , the three-week long east timor presidential campaign officially ends on the 12th .
voters will elect the first president on the 14th , who will become the first president when east timor officially becomes an independent country on may 20 .
presidential candidates running for the election include xanana gusmao and francisco do amaral .
gusmao was the leader of east timorese rebel forces while amaral was president of the short-lived " republic of east timor " established in november 1975 .
the two presidential candidates participated in a debate on the 11th in dili and answered various questions from voters .
gusmao has said that if he is elected , his priority is to solve the country 's economic problems . while amaral says he will ensure east timor to be a democratic country .
public opinion generally expects gusmao to win the election because he is regarded as the hero that brings independence to east timor .
with united nations ' support , east timor held a referendum on august 30 , 1999 and the absolute majority selected independence .
east timor officially elected a constituent assembly on august 30 last year and passed the first constitution for the country in march this year .
the new constitution will be effective when east timor officially becomes an independent country on may 20 this year . the constituent assembly will then become the first national council .
chinese foreign affairs confirm one chinese worker killed in jerusalem explosion
xinhua news agency , beijing , april 13 -- chinese foreign affairs spokeswoman zhang qiyue confirmed in beijing today that a chinese worker was killed in an explosion on the afternoon of april 12 at a public bus station in jerusalem . two other chinese workers were injured and one chinese worker was reported missing .
zhang qiyue said a suicide bombing took place at about 4 pm on april 12 at a public bus station in city center district of jerusalem . the explosion killed six and injured more than 70 .
in this bombing incident , one chinese worker was killed and two other chinese workers were injured . another chinese worker was reported missing .
she said the chinese embassy at israel attached high importance to the incident . the staff of the embassy accompanied the representative of the worker 's employer to the scene to identify the victim . embassy staff also visited the injured workers and gathered information about the matter . the embassy also discussed with relevant authorities on how to deal with problems or difficulties arising from the incident .
the embassy has also alerted chinese citizens and chinese enterprises in israel on the issue of personal safety and reminds them to take extra care when going out .
according to her , the chinese government regrets for the death of a chinese citizen in the explosion and has expressed condolence to the victim 's family .
the chinese government condemns any violent activities targeted at innocent civilians . the chinese government urges israeli-palestinian to adopt realistic measures to end the confrontation as soon as possible such as to prevent any further civilian injuries or deaths .
" the chinese government wishes to remind all chinese citizens and any personnel intending to travel to israel to re-consider their personal safety and to take necessary precaution . in case of an emergency , please promptly contact the chinese embassy at israel " , zhang qiyue said .
according to mena , the egyptian middle east news agency , the two foreign ministers have agreed in their telephone discussions that israel should take active response to the declaration by un , us , russia and european union , the so-called diplomatic ' quartet ' , and retreat its army immediately from the palestinian territory .
ahmed maher briefed josep pique about his meeting with yasser arafat on friday in the palestinian-controlled town ramallah .
maher said the palestinians are prepared to work with international community and find a way in accordance with relevant un resolutions that can end the israeli invasion into palestinian territory .
they agreed to maintain contacts with all parties concerned in order to find ways to thoroughly solve the conflicts in the middle east .
us state department spokesman richard boucher , who accompanied us secretary of state colin powell to visit the middle east , said earlier that day powell had canceled the planned meeting with arafat on march 13 in light of the explosion in jerusalem on april 12 .
but a us state department official , who declined to be named , said the meeting between powell and arafat would be delayed to april 14 .
meanwhile , maher also talked with syrian prime minister rafik hariri over the phone and exchanged views on the latest development in palestine .
uae pledges to bear all costs of rebuilding palestinian camp at jenin
xinhua , abu dhabi , april 13 ( reporter : xing xudong ) -- sheikh hamdan bin zayed al nahyan , minister of state for foreign affairs of united arab emirates , announced to the media on april 13 that united arab emirates ( uae ) would bear all the costs for rebuilding the jenin palestinian refugee camp which was destroyed by israeli army earlier . he said the reconstruction would commence as soon as possible such that the homeless can have a home again .
sheikh hamdan said the red crescent society of uae , which is responsible for the jenin camp reconstruction , have coordinated with the near orient and palestinian section of united nations relief and works agency . they have now drawn up concrete plans to rebuild the damaged buildings and utilities inside the camp .
uae have launched several nationwide fund raising campaigns since israel started large-scale military actions in palestinian towns on the west bank of jordan river , the minister of state added . so far , uae had raised 350 million durham ( nearly us $ 100 million ) .
comprehensive report -- chavez reclaims venezuela 's presidency
xinhua news agency , caracas , april 14 ( reporter : gu anping ) -- venezuelan president hugo chavez , who was held by a coup two days ago , has returned to presidential palace on the 14th . chavez swore again as president of bolivarian republic of venezuela amidst supporters ' cheers .
in a speech broadcasted nationwide on television , chavez thanked for the trust and support afforded him by the venezuelan people . he also expressed gratitude to organization of american states , treaty groups and 77-country consortium for their support of democracy as well as their efforts to condemn the coup . he also urged all venezuelan to resolve any difference in a peaceful way .
chavez emphasized that venezuela needs peace , stability and reasoning . all sides should do their best to stop any conflicts .
through the incident , " we have learned a lot of things . we will endeavor to correct past errors and mistakes . we will build a better country together " , chavez said .
venezuela had a military coup on the 11th . ten high-ranking military officers rescinded their support to chavez 's government . they also detained chavez .
pedro carmona , head of the venezuelan business association fedecamaras , was appointed temporary president of a transitional government on the 12th .
on the same day , chavez 's supporters held a peaceful rally in the capital city and demanded to reinstate chavez .
on the afternoon of the 13th , a group of soldiers loyal to chavez escorted chavez 's vice president , diosdado cabello , back to the presidential palace . cabello swore as temporary president on that evening and carmona resigned soon afterwards .
troops loyal to chavez issued an ultimatum to the coup for the release of chavez . loyal troops also took over the control of the strategic fuerte tiuna military barracks .
on the morning of the 14th , chavez was released from the small caribbean island where he was confined . he was taken by helicopter back to the presidential palace .
xinhua news agency , damascus , april 15 ( reporter : gong zhenxi ) -- syrian president bashar el assad held talks with the visiting u.s. secretary of state , colin powell on the 15th . the two sides discussed the latest developments in middle east , especially the serious situation in palestinian areas and the tensions on israel-lebanon border .
according to reports by syrian news agency , president bashar said in the meeting , " the events happening in palestine have caused a dead end to the ( middle east ) peace process . if we do not recognize this point , the situation may develop to an irreversible extent . at that time , we might have to wait for another generation . "
he pointed out that israel must withdraw from palestinian territories and stop killing any palestinian people . it is only then can israel talk about any peace process . "
he said , " peace can only be achieved when both sides are willing to come forth for it " .
he urged u.s. to adopt a clear position in the middle east peace process and play its role accordingly . this is necessary for a realistic execution of united nations ' resolutions .
as to the suicide bombings by palestinian , bashar said , " these actions are not the fundamental causes of the events in palestinian territory . they are consequences . they are strike backs against israeli actions " .
he pointed that the best method is to remove the fundamental causes for any tensions in palestine .
according to sources from diplomatic circle , powell and bashar also talked about problems on israel-lebanon border .
powell arrived damascus from beirut at noon on the 15th for a short visit in syria .
new york stock market closed lower
xinhua news agency , new york , april 15 -- investors are generally concerned with the prospects of corporate earnings after the news of unsatisfactory reports by citibank and continental airlines . new york stock market generally closed lower and the dow jones index fell to an eight-week low .
the dow jones industrial 30 index finished at 10,093.67 , down 97.15 points and is the lowest closing since february 22 . the nasdaq index , which is weighted heavily with tech stocks , lost 2.41 points and closed at 1,753.78 . standard & poor 's 500 index lost 8.46 points and closed at 1,102.55 .
furthermore , new york stock exchange composite index and the russell 2000 index , which tracks small companies , also closed lower . only american stock exchange composite index closed slightly higher .
the ratio of number of decline / advance stocks is 5 : 4 . volume has slid from the preceding day 's 1.26 billion shares to 1.12 billion shares .
during the day , citibank announced its failure to achieve target earning in the first quarter because of losses in argentina . continental airlines announced losses for its first quarter of operations too .
the news renewed investors ' concern for corporate earning reports due this week and market adopted a wait and see attitude .
wall street stock market fluctuated in a narrow range and finally closed lower for the day . turnover is also at a low level .
blue chips , citibank , continental airlines , general electric etc . , and tech stocks , microsoft , intel , cisco , oracle , dell and sun microsystem etc . , all closed lower .
colin powell will hold meeting with palestinian leader again
xinhua news agency , jerusalem , april 16 ( reporter : zhong cuihua ) -- u.s. secretary of state colin powell , who is currently in jerusalem on visit , is going to hold talks again with israeli prime minister sharon and chairman of palestinian authority arafat on the afternoon of 16th and in the morning of 17th .
according to reports here , powell postponed his departure from middle east for at least 24 hours in order to continue the mediation between israel and palestine .
powell says he hopes israel and palestine can issue a joint statement condemning terrorist attacks against israeli and the palestinian people . he urges that the state of palestine be built through negotiations and the fight against terrorism should continue .
on the 15th , powell concluded his one-day visit to lebanon and syria and returned to israel . on late evening that day , he cancelled the plan to hold a special meeting with arafat on the 16th .
powell has told the press that u.s. supports the proposal made by sharon for the convention of a regional peace conference . he thinks that the meeting can be at minister level and arafat can send a high level delegation to attend .
arafat has already indicated palestinian can accept the proposal of a regional peace meeting only if israel withdraws immediately from all palestinian territories in the west bank of jordan river
powell held a meeting with sharon on the 12th .
on the 14th , he went to the west bank city ramallah where arafat was surrounded by israeli army and held a meeting with the palestinian leader .
on that night , he briefed sharon with the details of the meeting with arafat .
unhcr visits afghanistan
xinhua news agency , kabul , april 16 ( reporter : shang xuqian ) -- united nations high commissioner of refugee ( unhcr ) ruud lubbers , now on visit in afghanistan , met interim afghan leader hamid karzai and discussed about how to resettle afghan refugees back into afghan society .
unhcr office issued a press release on april 16 saying that lubbers stressed the resettlement of refugees back into the society is an important step to restore stability in afghanistan .
he stressed that the safety of refugees seeking to return home have to be guaranteed . the safety in rural areas is very important failing that a large amount of refugees will flock to cities .
karzai thanked the unhcr office for its works in afghanistan over the years .
he said resettlement of refugees back into the society is a main area of work for the interim government .
he stressed that the return of homeless people to their hometowns is a problem requiring urgent attention .
given that most regions in afghanistan are now stable and together with abundant rainfalls at this moment , he thinks these people can start farming immediately after they arrive home and be self sufficient in food .
according to unhcr spokesman yusuf hassan , more than 240,000 afghans had returned to afghanistan from pakistan ever since unhcr and afghan interim government officially started to assist refugees to go back to their hometowns . in addition , more than 5,000 people went home from iran and 4,000 returned from tajikistan .
among them , 40 per cent went to cities .
lubbers arrived afghanistan after he completed his visit in iran .
he will visit pakistan on april 17 .
in the second round of badminton euro 2002 , some seeded players start to be eliminated
xinhua news agency , stockholm , april 17 ( reporter : wu ping ) -- badminton euro 2002 entered its second round of competition in malmo , a southern city of sweden . there were five individual contests today .
with the exception of the mixed doubles , all other individual events eliminated some seeded players .
in men 's singles , peter rasmussen of denmark eliminated the british seeded player colin haughton .
in women 's singles , juliane schenk of germany eliminated seeded tine rasmussen of denmark .
in men 's doubles , a russian pair eliminated the seeded pair joakim andersson / johan holm .
in women 's doubles , the wales seeded pair felicity gallup / joanne muggeridge was eliminated by a polish / belaruse pair .
according to schedule , five individual events will start the third round and quarterfinals tomorrow .
semi-finals and finals will be held on april 19 and 20 respectively .
palestine condemns israeli army 's continued violation on palestinian people
xinhua news agency , gaza , april 18 ( reporter : du zhen ) -- palestinian national authority released a statement on the 17th to condemn israeli army 's continued violations on palestinian people in the west bank of jordan river and the gaza strip . the statement criticized israeli prime minister sharon 's abuse of military forces and accused his policy has effectively " strangled any peace hope in the region " .
the statement cited " israeli government and its prime minister sharon 's refusal to withdraw from palestinian cities and terminate all military actions there " as the principal reason for u.s. secretary of state powell 's middle east mediation failure .
israeli army continues to control most palestinian cities in the west bank of jordan river on that day .
eyewitnesses said israeli armored division did once pull out of jenin on that day but returned to the city after a short while . israeli army has then re-occupied the center of the city .
according to reports by israeli radio stations , israeli army has killed one palestinian in an israeli settlement in south gaza region .
palestinian official said that the palestinian was shot while passing by the settlement .
on the other hand , israeli army said the man and several other armed palestinian attempted to attack the settlement and was killed by israeli soldiers .
russian president 's address to federal assembly
xinhua news agency , moscow , april 18 -- russian president vladimir putin issued his address to both houses of parliament on the 18th . he pointed out that russia should aim to strengthen its economy and become a competitive country . russia has to build constructive and normal relations with different countries in the world such that russia can become a genuine member of the international community .
putin said russia 's development objective is to build a democratic country and a civilized market economy . the most important thing is to improve the living standard of the russian people .
in his summary of achievements for past year , he pointed out that russian economy has continued to grow . unemployment has decreased and living standard is generally improving . the russian people are now more confident about their future than before .
putin expressed satisfaction with the good operating budgets and the continued improvement in operating environments in the past two years .
he specially emphasized that russia 's oil production has now reached the second place in the world and ranks number one in terms of volume of energy resources trading .
putin also elaborated russia 's development plan for the year as well as some internal and external policies .
this is putin 's third presidential address to the two parliaments since his appointment .
there are over 1000 representatives attending the meeting including 600 deputies of duma , 89 members of federation council , staff of presidential office and heads of government departments .
china 's foreign affairs spokeswoman commented on a resolution passed by european parliament
xinhua news agency , beijing , april 19 -- china 's foreign affairs spokeswoman , zhang qiyue , commented on a resolution passed by the european parliament ( ep ) during an answering session for reporters .
a reporter asked , " on april 11 , european parliament considered and passed the ' european parliament on eu strategy towards china ' resolution .
what are the comments of the chinese government ? "
zhang qiyue answered , " the chinese government noted that ep has recently passed this resolution .
the resolution is of the opinion that china and europe union ( eu ) have a lot of common interests . it advocates that china and eu should develop a cooperative partnership and strengthen bilateral contacts , communication and dialogue . both sides should expand trades and cooperate in technology , education and cultural exchanges etc .
we welcome such positive views .
however , the resolution adopts an incorrect position and has ignored facts on a range of issues including taiwan , tibet and human rights in china . such statements constitute a serious interference in china 's internal affairs . the chinese government cannot accept these statements .
we hope that ep will strictly adhere to the one-china policy and devote more efforts to promote bilateral relations . otherwise , the relation between china and eu may be negatively impacted . "
kidnapped official of indian high commission in pakistan released
xinhua news agency , new delhi , april 19 ( reporter : xiong changyi ) -- indian foreign affairs ministry spokeswoman nirupama rao said in the evening of april 19 that anil khanna , an official working for the indian high commission in islamabad , was abducted on friday morning and was subsequently released this afternoon .
pakistani police returned khanna to indian officials in a local police station after they notified indian high commission about the release , rao said .
khanna had been seriously beaten and was admitted hospital .
she said pakistani police refused to list the case as abduction , which arose suspicion that the inter-services intelligence agency of pakistan was behind the abduction .
khanna was abducted in the morning of 19th when he was taking a bus to office .
indian foreign affairs issued a statement protesting strongly to the pakistani authorities over the abduction of an indian high commission official under broad daylight in pakistan .
enterprises in hebei province actively apply for foreign trade rights
xinhua news agency , shijia zhuang , april 20 ( reporter : rao yajie ) -- according to information from economic and foreign trade office of hebei province , more than 200 enterprises from different trades in the province have registered with their office or otherwise have obtained approval from the ministry of foreign trade and economic cooperation ( moftec ) for foreign trade rights so far this year . the number of foreign trade rights registration is 2.3 times of the preceding year .
according to introduction , there are 39 foreign trading companies registered during the period and among them 17 are private owned foreign trading companies .
in addition , there are several dozens of commercial , material , supply / marketing enterprises and state-owned collective enterprises registered for the right .
seventy-seven private production enterprises have also applied for foreign trade rights .
more and more private enterprises have registered for foreign trade rights , which is a good sign for the province .
in july last year , moftec has further relaxed the terms and standards for export rights applicable to all kinds of enterprises . the approval system is replaced by a registration system . the new regulations impose a uniform management system and a common standard amongst all types of production or commercial enterprises irrespective of their capital forms . many enterprises are encouraged by the new rules and actively apply for registration .
israel will cooperate in united nations investigation
xinhua news agency , jerusalem , april 20 ( reporter : zhong cuihua and ming dajun ) -- an official of israel government indicated on the 20th that related departments will cooperate with united nations ( un ) inquiry team . un intends to send a fact-finding team to discover the truth about what went on inside jenin refugee camp .
israeli radio station quoted a government official as saying israel will provide un delegation with videotapes showing the operations taken place in jenin refugee camp . israel will let the delegation to interview soldiers and commanding officers participated in the action . israel hopes the team can be fair and objective throughout the investigation process .
the security council of un has unanimously passed the u.s. proposal , which suggests the dispatch of a fact-finding team to discover the truth at jenin refugee camp .
several hours before the voting , israeli foreign minister josep pique has called un secretary-general annan by phone . pique indicated that israel welcome un delegation to " clarify " the truth at jenin refugee camp .
annan has also talked with israeli defense minister binyamin ben-eliezer over phone . ben-eliezer also indicated that israel has no objection to an un investigation .
it is understood that both ben-eliezer and pique said israeli soldiers have encountered palestinian armed personnel whilst in action at jenin refugee camp . both sides exchanged gunfire . twenty-three israeli soldiers were killed and fifty palestinian , mostly armed personnel , were killed in the conflict .
recently , international community has stepped up the demand for an investigation on jenin refugee camp , where the most serious conflict took place .
palestinian accuses israeli soldiers of massacring several hundred palestinian there . however , israel denies the accusation .
china expresses strong dissatisfaction over junichiro koizumi 's visit to yasukuni shrine
xinhua news agency , beijing , april 21 -- " china firmly opposes japanese leader 's visit to yasukuni shrine , which honors class a war criminals , in any way and at any time " , china 's foreign affairs spokeswoman , zhang qiyue said here in beijing today .
china expresses strong dissatisfaction to japanese leader 's recent visit .
in her comments on japanese prime minister junichiro koizumi 's visit this morning to yasukuni shrine , zhang qiyue pointed out such visit can only damage the image of japan . it is going to make it more difficult for japan to earn the trust of the people throughout asia on its many problems in history .
this is koizumi 's second visit to yasukuni shrine since he became prime minister .
yasukuni shrine was built to honor war dead in past battles since meiji restoration ( most of the wars were results of japanese aggression ) . hideki tojo , who was convicted as a class a war criminal after world war ii , is also honored in the shrine .
france holds the first-round of presidential election
xinhua news agency , paris , april 21 ( reporter : liang guihe ) -- france holds the first-round of presidential election on the 21st and more than 64 thousand poll stations across the country opened their doors to voters at 8 am .
there are 40 million voters and they have to pick the fifth republic - france 's seventh president amongst the sixteen candidates .
the polling results will be known on the same evening .
according to french interior department , the voting rate was 21.4 % as of noon on the 21st , which is lower than the 22.52 % in the first-round of the presidential election in 1995 .
according to forecasts by local media , the voting rate this year may reach a historical low .
the french constitution requires a candidate to obtain 51 % or more of all votes in the first-round . otherwise , the two candidates with the highest votes will enter the second-round of voting on may 5 .
according to the public opinion poll last friday , the present president jacques chirac and prime minister lionel jospin may win the first-round with more or less the same number of votes .
that is because there are a total of 16 candidates for the election , which is a historical record on its own . hence , it is expected that votes will be split amongst candidtates .
the right wing national front leader jean-marie le pen may win the third place in the first-round . it is also possible that he may " unexpectedly " end up in the first two places .
u.s. may help train georgia 's soldiers
xinhua news agency , moscow , april 22 ( reporter : zhou liang ) -- according to news from tbilisi : georgia 's president eduard shevardnadze denies on the 22nd about reports that u.s. has refused to train georgia 's army .
according to itar-tass , eduard shevardnadze made the denial in a press conference held in tbilisi .
he said that u.s. and georgia has not made any changes to an agreement pursuant to which u.s. military experts will help train georgia 's army . it is only that a specific date has not been agreed for the experts ' arrival in georgia .
according to him , u.s. military experts are making preparation for their trip to georgia . they will be in georgia sooner or later .
he also pointed out that u.s.-georgia 's military cooperation is not directed against russia .
it is understood that u.s. military experts is going to train 4 barracks and 1 company of georgian soldiers under the agreement between the two countries .
foreign press association in israel demands the return of confiscated press cards
xinhua news agency , jerusalem , april 22 ( reporter : zhong cuihua ) -- the foreign press association in israel has released a statement on the 22nd demanding the return of press cards for at least 17 reporters that were confiscated by israeli army at the city of bethlehem , west bank of jordan river .
according to the statement , an israeli army officer confiscated a batch of press cards that belongs to foreign reporters and palestinians working for international news agencies at a spot approximately 400 meters from the church where jesus was born . the reason given was that the area was a closed security zone . however , the officer did not show any document to prove his point .
the statement pointed out that israel is trying to restrict media from reporting the standoff between palestinian militia and israeli army at the church of the nativity , where it is generally believed to be the birthplace of jesus christ .
on april 2 , israeli army entered and occupied bethlehem . they tried to surround more than 200 palestinian militias , who then hid themselves inside the church of nativity . the standoff has continued till today .
hindu followers soften stance on peaceful praying ceremony
comprehensive report , ayodhya , india -- hundreds of hindu followers in white gowns held a peaceful praying ceremony yesterday at a sacred place in ayodhya under the supervision of riot police .
hindu leader mahant ramachandra paramhans , who advocated the construction of a hindu temple on the site of a former mosque , handed over a sacred stone to a government official just outside an area banned for any religious ceremony by the supreme court .
paramhans threatened the day before yesterday that he would disregard the court order and hold a praying ceremony there .
however , he suddenly softened his stance yesterday . he indicated that the praying gathering would be held at another place in ayhdhya .
according to reports in local media , the 93 years old paramhans changed his mind after the ruling bharatiya janata party exerted pressure .
before that , indian authorities have dispatched additional army and police officers to this northern city on fears that hindu extremists might disregard court order and hold a praying gathering at the site of the former mosque .
one-fourth of deputies voted no or abstained from voting to the report
deputies of national people 's congress are not satisfied with the reform in judicial system
( reporter : zhou ruipeng ) -- there are more than one-fourth of no-votes or abstentions on the work report of supreme people 's court and supreme people 's procuratorate in yesterday 's meeting of the national people 's congress ( npc ) . the result indicates their dissatisfaction with the achievements in the reform and development of the judicial system ,
however , 2742 out of the 2813 deputies attending the 5th session of the ninth national people 's congress voted yes to the work report of zhu rongji 's government . the endorsing rate remains high at 97.5 % , which is about the same as last year .
it is expected that zhu rongji will step down from the highest decision making layer as well as from the politburo standing committee this autumn after china holds the 16th five-yearly communist party congress . zhu has publicly indicated that he wants to retire .
however , the result of votes indicates zhu rongji is still well respected by deputies notwithstanding he may lose his power soon .
the meeting has lasted for 10-1 / 2 days and the 2002 fiscal budget with a deficit of renminbi 309.8 billions ( about 68.8 billion singapore dollars ) was passed yesterday with 80.5 % of yes votes .
on the other hand , the report prepared by li peng , chairman of the standing committee of npc on the work of the standing committee has encountered more no-votes or abstentions than last year .
the report of the standing committee of npc has received 2587 yes-votes , 112 no-votes and 114 abstentions in yesterday 's voting .
in the last year , that same report had 2582 yes-votes , 85 no-votes and 122 abstentions .
notwithstanding the response of deputies of npc is slightly better than last year , there are still 28 % and 27 % of npc deputies voted no or abstained from voting on the work report of supreme people 's court and supreme people 's procuratorate yesterday .
the work report by xiao yang , president of supreme people 's court obtained 2026 yes-votes , 528 no-votes and 259 abstentions .
in last year , xiao 's report obtained 1953 yes-votes , 530 no-votes and 306 abstentions .
the work report of han zhubin , procurator-general of supreme people 's procuratorate obtained 2044 yes-votes , 516 no-votes and 253 abstentions .
in last year , han 's report obtained 1873 yes-votes , 584 no-votes and 332 abstentions .
since this year is the last session of the current npc , a new selection is needed next year . therefore , deputies have also passed the " decision on number and election of deputies for the tenth national people 's congress " in the closing session yesterday . the resolution requires new members of the tenth npc to be selected before end of january next year .
china will accelerate the changeover of local party and government heads
( hong kong ) -- information source closed to beijing 's " two meetings " has disclosed to ' mingpao ' : china will accelerate the changeover of local party and government heads after the conclusion of national people 's congress and people 's political consultative conference .
the central government has requested local governments to complete changeover work before june this year . there are currently a total of 17 provinces , municipality directly under the jurisdiction of the central government and autonomous regions that have not completed the formation of a new management team .
according to the source , the central government has established an appointment standard . all leaders in party and local government at provincial level or higher must possess undergraduate studies in his / her own specialization together with a bachelor or higher degree from a university .
according to the regulations of central government , secretary-general of a province must be younger than 59 . on the other hand , the head of a province has to be younger than 56 .
after the local government changeovers , party appointed secretaries will serve concurrently as head of the people 's congress of a similar level . the measure is to strengthen the communist party 's control over people 's congress leadership at different levels .
the information source also pointed out that sixty-two party leaders in thirty-one provinces , autonomous regions and direct municipality have been replaced or transferred since march last year .
amongst these changes , fourteen provinces have completed the local party head adjustments . this includes changes to the party appointed secretary in the six provinces of mongolia , jiangxi , hubei , hainan , yunnan and qinghai .
for provincial , direct municipality and autonomous region governments , eleven provincial level officials have been transferred . this includes the head of province or head of city for shanghai , jiangxi , shandong , hunan and yunnan .
us embassy in yemen attacked by grenade , one youth arrested , no one injured
comprehensive report , san 'a -- a yemeni youth threw a grenade into the us embassy in yemen , yemeni and us officials said . the youth was arrested immediately and no one was injured in the incident .
us embassy in italy received a postal parcel with white powder in it .
in rome , the us embassy received a parcel containing white powder the day before yesterday . embassy officials feared that it might contain anthrax spores .
an embassy spokesman said they had sent the parcel to the biochemical expert team of the local fire-fighting department for analysis . the result will be announced next week .
an official of yemeni interior ministry said on the state-owned television that sameer yahia awadh , 25 , threw a grenade against the wall of the us embassy , which is located in the northeastern district of the capital city , san 'a .
he said awadh came from the qada 'al mahwit province 60 km northwest of san 'a and had another grenade when he was arrested .
the official said this grenade attack had not resulted in any casualties or property damages to the embassy .
witnesses said police encircled areas around the embassy after the grenade exploded .
in washington , the department of state spokesman richard boucher said initial investigation found no damage to the embassy and no one was injured .
yemeni authority apprehended the suspect .
the yemeni authorities said the grenade was not thrown inside the enclosing walls of the embassy .
new york and london stock markets went up
