investors believe profitability of enterprises will improve in tandem with a recovery in u.s. economy . the largest retail chain group , wal-mart and credit card company , american express inspired a rally . the dow recorded the longest period of weekly advances since september 2000 .
the dow jones industrial closed at 10,607.23 on friday , up 90.09 or 0.9 % .
nasdaq index closed at 1,868.30 , up 14.16 or 0.8 % . the standard & poor 's 500 index , which tracks a broader market , closed at 1,166.16 , up 13.12 or 1.1 % .
for the whole week , the dow went up by 0.3 % and the accumulated increase since beginning of year has expanded to 5.8 % .
standard & poor 's 500 index went up 0.2 % . on the other hand , nasdaq index was 3.2 % lower , which was first time it showed a decline in the past three weeks .
