beijing attacked by another serious sandstorm
agence france presse , beijing -- according to chinese state media , beijing had another serious sandstorm yesterday .
despite costly environmental efforts to halt the advance of the desert to beijing , sandstorms continue their frequent annual assault on the capital city . sandstorms look like to remain a serious challenge to beijing , which is going to host the 2008 olympics .
according to china meteorological administration 's forecasts , the year 's first sandstorm struck beijing last friday with further windy cold fronts from the mongolian steppe expected to shroud beijing in a yellow , dusty haze .
" i cannot say sandstorms won 't occur in 2008 , " yang weixi ( transliteration ) , chief engineer of the desertification control center of china 's ministry of forestry told the beijing weekend publication .
" what we can do is to manage the man-made factors which cause sandstorms and the expansion of desertification , " he said .
however , conditions beyond human control , like wind , drought and huge existing deserts , would make it impossible to get rid of the storms in a short time frame , yang said .
the chinese government has committed to spend renminbi 56.8 billion ( about singapore dollars 12.376 billion ) to curb desertification and lessen sandstorms between 2002 and 2008 .
beijing alone will spend approximately renminbi 1 billion ( about singapore dollars 220 million ) this year .
" the increase in funding will greatly improve the situation , but ... it may take decades to see a gradual improvement , " an expert of the china forestry research institute said .
chinese environmentalists raised alarm bells after a survey earlier this year , which found almost a third of the country 's land mass is now desert largely due to human economic activity , such as livestock overgrazing .
in the first six months of 2001 , beijing was hit by 18 sandstorms originating from inner mongolia , where 60 percent of the land is desert , the survey said .
national people 's congress lawmakers from shanghai , beijing and inner mongolia , who met in beijing this month , have urged the government to set up a " green wall " of trees to block the dust storms .
the vice president of the geographical society of china , xu shiyuan , warned that if the government failed to take action , sandstorms could blow as far as shanghai , the shanghai star newspaper said .
forged diplomas are flooding china ; some cadres on the job are also holding forged diploma
comprehensive report , hong kong -- false diplomas are flooding mainland china . guangdong college graduate career center has completed the verification of academic certificates held by fifteen government officials submitted to the center by a city in chao-shan regions . seven of them can be confirmed to be a forgery simply through visual examination .
according to reports in hong kong newspapers , the center commenced verification services since may this year . it has so far examined more than 3,500 certificates and more than 800 certificates are found to be forgeries of one kind or the other . that is a forging rate of 23 % .
according to the reports , most of the forged certificates relate to adult education and self-study examination certificates . approximately two-third are forged in the street and the other one-third are forged by formal educational institutions .
at the time the center was first established , many institutions are in the process of reform . hence , units of organizations or enterprises have submitted the bulk of the certificates for verification . in many cases , the owners of the forged certificates are actually cadres currently on the job , the officer-in-charge of the center said .
at present , guangdong college graduate career center is the only institution authorized by the related department of china 's ministry of education to provide higher education qualification verification services in china
in one occasion , to facilitate decision on selecting officer , a municipal level state-owned bank has sent in 36 diplomas of middle-level officers and some key cadres for verification . the result is that only 6 diplomas are genuine , the officer-in-charge said .
it is understood that many private enterprises have also employed the verification services and their main interests are diplomas of job applicants and newly recruited university students .
the verification department has also found many forged university credentials
last year , a large enterprise has recruited a large batch of university students for its branch office in zhu jiang delta area .
the boss has sent in the credentials of more than 30 employees for verification and it was found that ten of them were forgeries .
in recent years , many educational institutions from rest of china have established a branch office in guangdong . these institutions have no rights to confer educational qualification . however , these institutions frequently play tricks to attract more students and claim that they can confer certificates recognized by the state . when students graduate , these institutions have to make a batch of forged certificates for the students .
