there were not so many north koreans in beijing in the past . also , unlike those from xinjiang and henan , who often involve in criminal acts , north koreans were not key monitoring targets of the authorities .
reportedly , public security has ' invited ' the german doctor , who has assisted the 25 north koreans , to their office for a ' talk ' right after the incident on march 14 . soon afterwards , public security has sent him to the airport and the doctor has to leave immediately .
after the doctor is gone , public security and the state security department have conducted an internal review .
the review involved two main areas : first , security in the embassy areas , and second , the management of north koreans in beijing .
meanwhile , the authorities have also requested relevant departments in jilin areas to take more effective measures to stop illegal north korea immigrants from getting to beijing .
sand and dust covered the sky of pyongyang and seoul ; yellow sand everywhere in the korean peninsula
comprehensive report from pyongyang and seoul -- the sandstorm just swept across northern china hit the korean peninsula fiercely yesterday . a massive cloud of brownish yellow dust covered most regions including pyongyang , the north korea capital and seoul , the south korea capital .
according to xinhua news agency , a powerful sandstorm attacked pyongyang yesterday in early morning .
since dawn , a massive cloud of brownish yellow dust covered pyongyang .
this is the first sandstorm in north korea since spring this year .
six air routes were disrupted .
meanwhile , according to reports of beijing people 's net , a huge ' sandstorm ' occurred in south korea yesterday . with the exception of inchon international airport , six domestic air routes were disrupted .
' sandstorm ' occurred all over south korea .
according to tests by the ministry of environment , the level of fine dust in the sky of seoul has reached 1000 micrograms per cubic meter by noon yesterday . that is 17 times higher than the normal level and is the highest level ever recorded .
affected by the nationwide dusty weather , only inchon international airport operated normally in south korea . six domestic air routes including taegu , ulsan , pohang and others were disrupted . passengers of more than 30 flights were forced to use other means of transportations .
according to the associated press , south korea government has ordered kindergartens and elementary schools to cancel classes for the day because of excessive level of fine dust in the air . the measure is intended to protect children from polluted air .
yellow dust weather has already occurred three times in seoul , korea this year .
according to the forecast by korea meteorological administration yesterday , ' the strong rising atmospheric current originated from china and the desert regions of mongolia caused a large amount of dust hanging in the air over northern china and the dust have entered korea through the northwester wind . '
large enough to flatten an average city , asteroid brushed past the earth at close shave
associated press , melbourne and florida -- an asteroid , large enough to flatten an average city , brushed past the earth within a short range of 463,000 kilometers , but was not discovered in time . it was four days after the close shave could astronomers tell about it .
this asteroid , about 50 meters in diameter , was flying from the direction of the sun , thus astronomers could hardly detect it .
the asteroid brushed past the earth on march 8 , but was not detected until march 12 when the asteroid was gone .
williams of the international astronomical union 's minor planet center in cambridge , massachusetts , has helped in determining the astronomical position of this asteroid .
from the astronomical point of view , this asteroid was very close to the earth because the moon is only 402,000 kilometers away from the earth .
williams on wednesday spoke to ' florida today ' , " the key is to detect asteroids before they are flying from the direction of the sun . "
thus , astronomers can determine an asteroid 's orbit sooner , predicting whether it will hit the earth or not .
when an asteroid of similar size hit the earth in 1908 , it blasted out a crater of 32 kilometers wide in the forest of siberia .
interior minister confirmed italian government senior advisor shot dead by ' red brigades '
agence france presse , rome - italian interior minister scajola confirmed the day before yesterday that italian government senior advisor biagi was shot dead by a sect of the leftist guerrilla group ' red brigades ' .
scajola said that the two gunmen even used a similar pistol that was used in another political assassination 3 years ago to gun down biagi .
on the other side , italian prime minister silvio berlusconi , after biagi 's assassination , has voluntarily invited union leaders to return to the negotiating table for discussions on biagi 's proposed labor reform plan .
the 52-year-old labor ministry advisor was an economist and a professor in the science of law .
he was on tuesday night shot to death by two motorcyclists outside his home in the northern city of bologna right after he biked home . the news shocked the italian political circles .
biagi had helped in drafting a labor reform proposal that provoked strong protests from labor unions and the leftists .
they thought that the proposal would make it easier for employers to layoff workers .
a witness said that biagi was lying in a pool of blood , with his briefcase on the side .
red brigades ' five-star symbol has been engraved on the door of biagi 's home . however , it is not known at this moment when that was done .
formed in 1973 , red brigades were suspected of carrying out a series of bombings and assassinations in the 70s and 80s , including the kidnapping and killing of former prime minister aldo moro in 1978 .
chinese-american engineer sentenced to 5 years imprisonment for illegally obtaining china 's state secrets and paying bribes
associated press , beijing -- the beijing no. 1 people 's intermediate court yesterday sentenced chinese-american engineer fang fuming to 5 years imprisonment . fang was convicted for illegally obtaining state secrets and paying bribes on behalf of a company .
this case has brought about us protests .
a us embassy spokesman said that fang fuming would be deported after serving the sentence .
the prison term would be adjusted to reflect the time he has been detained .
the us embassy has sent a diplomat to attend the trial .
fang fuming 's lawyer said that his client has already been detained for 2 years , but china said not that long .
xinhua news agency confirmed the sentence .
the agency said that fang fuming obtained 35 documents containing state secrets from 1995 to 1999 . fang gave chinese state workers usd245,000 ( about 450,000 singapore dollars in current value ) in bribes so as to assist foreign investors in bidding for chinese power projects .
fang fuming was an electrical engineering consultant for foreign companies in china and also elsewhere in asia .
fang fuming 's lawyer cohen said that fang fuming denied paying bribes , claiming himself being the victim of the corrupted chinese power officials .
fang fuming used to be an official in china 's electrical authority until he became a us citizen in 1994 .
in the past 2 years , a number of american citizens and residents have been charged with violating the chinese national security laws , and fang fuming being one of them .
fang fuming 's detention has once caused tensions to sino-us relations .
the us government has repeatedly protested to china over her way of handling the fang fuming case . authorities have detained fang for months without putting him to trial , which is a violation of international standards .
fang fuming 's family said that he has been treated badly .
his wife and two children are us citizens .
cohen said that fang fuming was detained on february 28 , 2000 . however , china 's foreign ministry gave the detention date as august 28 , 2000 .
china has cancelled the fleet visit to the us , without confirming if hu jintao 's visit to us will proceed as scheduled
comprehensive report , beijing -- the once warming up sino-us relations attained by us president bush 's china visit is rapidly cooling off . china confirmed yesterday the cancellation of its fleet visit to us ports this year . china also refused to say if vice president hu jintao would visit us as scheduled .
when asked in a press conference , chinese foreign ministry spokeswoman zhang qiyue said , " as much as i know , chinese navel vessels are preparing their fleet for visits as planned . however , us ports are not on their plans . "
when questioned by a reporter twice if hu jintao 's scheduled trip to the us would be affected , zhang qiyue did not comment or confirm . she also made no further comments on requests to clarify whether her answer earlier to a question can be interpreted as saying hu jintao 's april visit to the us would take place as planned .
zhang qiyue merely accused the us side for repeatedly ' violating the promises laid out in the three sino-us joint communiques in a series of moves ' just within a month after bush 's china visit . she also requested the us side ' to stop using the taiwan issue in meddling china 's internal affairs . '
on the other side , in washington on wednesday , the us paid no attention to china 's warning about the ' icy breeze ' being blown over sino-us relations . us insisted that there is nothing wrong to allow taiwan 's defense minister to attend the ' us-taiwan defense summit ' in florida .
beijing has criticized us repeatedly in granting visa to taiwan 's defense minister tang yiauming for attending a conference organized by the us weapons industry earlier this month .
tang yiauming also met two us senior officials during his time in us .
in a news briefing , the state department spokesman boucher was questioned by reporters about china 's protests against this matter . however , he apparently tried to avoid opening up a verbal battle with china .
he said , " after this conference , our position is clear to all .
if you want to ask me about this matter every day , i am willing to explain it every day . if china wants to ask this matter every day , we are willing to explain it every day . "
he said , " the position has never changed . this is our normal contact with the people of taiwan and we will keep on doing it . "
zhang qiyue also confirmed yesterday a report by the russian media that president jiang zemin was requested by russian president putin to hold a telephone conversation with him the night before . the two sides exchanged opinions on the issue of sino-russian mutual cooperation .
both sides do believe that carrying out sino-russian mutual cooperation is in the interest of both countries and their people .
